flist|refs=\n<ref name=\"toponymie\">{{toponymie |1229}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Amos, Quebec}}\n*[http://www.ville.amos.qc.ca Ville d'Amos]\n\n{{Geographic location\n | title = <big>Adjacent Municipal Subdivisions</big>\n | Centre    = Amos''' <br> (completely surrounds [[Pikogan, Quebec|Pikogan]])\n | North     = [[Saint-F\u00e9lix-de-Dalquier, Quebec|Saint-F\u00e9lix-de-Dalquier]], [[Saint-Dominique-du-Rosaire, Quebec|Saint-Dominique-du-Rosaire]]\n | Northeast = \n | East      = [[La Morandi\u00e8re, Quebec|La Morandi\u00e8re]]\n | Southeast = [[Landrienne, Quebec|Landrienne]]\n | South     = [[Saint-Mathieu-d'Harricana, Quebec|Saint-Mathieu-d'Harricana]], [[Saint-Marc-de-Figuery, Quebec|Saint-Marc-de-Figuery]]\n | Southwest = \n | West      = [[Tr\u00e9cesson, Quebec|Tr\u00e9cesson]]<br>[[Sainte-Gertrude-Manneville, Quebec|Sainte-Gertrude-Manneville]]\n | Northwest = \n | image     =\n}}\n{{Abitibi RCM|state=expanded}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Quebec]]\n[[Category:Amos, Quebec| ]]\n", "name_user": "Mattximus", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amos,_Quebec"}
{"title_page": "Tenorio Volcano", "text_new": "{{Infobox mountain\n| name = Tenorio Volcano \n| photo = \n| photo_caption = \n| elevation_m = 1916\n| elevation_ref = \n| prominence_m = \n| map = Costa Rica\n| map_caption = Costa Rica\n| label_position = right\n| location = Border between [[Alajuela Province]] and [[Guanacaste Province]], [[Costa Rica]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|10.672778|N|85.015|W|type:mountain_region:CR_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| range_coordinates = \n| coordinates_ref = \n| topo = \n| type = [[Stratovolcano]] \n| age = \n| last_eruption = \n| first_ascent = \n| easiest_route = \n}}\n\n'''Tenorio Volcano''' ({{lang-es|Volc\u00e1n Tenorio}}) is an inactive [[andesite|andesitic]] [[stratovolcano]] in north-western [[Costa Rica]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Alvarado Induni |first1=Guillermo |title=Los volcanes de Costa Rica |publisher=Editorial de la Universidad Estatal a Distancia |isbn=978-9968-316-79-8 |pages=92-98}}</ref>\n\n== Toponymy ==\n\nThe name comes from the [[Chorotega]] legend of Eskameca and Tenor\u00ed. The name in its current form is first mentioned in a 1744 document, further in 1745 by historian Le\u00f3n Fern\u00e1ndez Bonilla.\n\n== Physical aspects ==\n\nIt is composed of four volcanic peaks and two twin craters,  one of the craters is sometimes referred to as the Montezuma Volcano.<ref name=gvp>{{cite gvp|vnum=345031|title=Tenorio}}</ref> The formation occupies a 225 km\u00b2 area. In the lowest areas thre is [[savanna]], [[rain forest]] in the middle areas and [[cloud forest]] at the top. \n\nThe rivers Tenorio, Tenorito and Martirio have their source in this volcano. \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Volcanoes of Costa Rica}}\n{{Mountains of Costa Rica}}\n{{Central American volcanoes}}\n\n[[Category:Stratovolcanoes]]\n[[Category:Volcanoes of Costa Rica]]\n\n{{CostaRica-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox mountain\n| name = Tenorio Volcano \n| photo = \n| photo_caption = \n| elevation_m = 1916\n| elevation_ref = \n| prominence_m = \n| map = Costa Rica\n| map_caption = Costa Rica\n| label_position = right\n| location = Border between [[Alajuela Province]] and [[Guanacaste Province]], [[Costa Rica]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|10.672778|N|85.015|W|type:mountain_region:CR_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| range_coordinates = \n| coordinates_ref = \n| topo = \n| type = [[Stratovolcano]] \n| age = \n| last_eruption = \n| first_ascent = \n| easiest_route = \n}}\n\n'''Tenorio Volcano''' ({{lang-es|Volc\u00e1n Tenorio}}) is an inactive [[andesite|andesitic]] [[stratovolcano]] in north-western [[Costa Rica]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Alvarado Induni |first1=Guillermo |title=Los volcanes de Costa Rica |publisher=Editorial de la Universidad Estatal a Distancia |isbn=978-9968-316-79-8 |pages=92-98}}</ref>\n\n== Toponymy ==\n\nThe name comes from the [[Chorotega]] legend of Eskameca and Tenor\u00ed. The name in its current form is first mentioned in a 1744 document, further in 1745 by historian Le\u00f3n Fern\u00e1ndez Bonilla.\n\n== Physical aspects ==\n\nIt is composed of four volcanic peaks and two twin craters,  one of the craters is sometimes referred to as the Montezuma Volcano.<ref name=gvp>{{cite gvp|vnum=1405-031|title=Tenorio}}</ref> The formation occupies a 225 km\u00b2 area. In the lowest areas thre is [[savanna]], [[rain forest]] in the middle areas and [[cloud forest]] at the top. \n\nThe rivers Tenorio, Tenorito and Martirio have their source in this volcano. \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Volcanoes of Costa Rica}}\n{{Mountains of Costa Rica}}\n{{Central American volcanoes}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of volcanoes|Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:Volcanoes of Costa Rica| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of landforms of Costa Rica|Volcanoes]]\n", "name_user": "Darwinek", "label": "safe", "comment": "link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tenorio_Volcano"}
